message.content:
1. The study is a randomized sham-controlled cross-over study.
2. The study involved 60 subjects.
3. Out of the 60 subjects, 30 were males.
4. The subjects received both sham and active tDCS.
5. The subjects were divided into two subgroups.
6. One subgroup received anode left/cathode right tDCS.
7. The other subgroup received anode right/cathode left tDCS.
8. The tDCS was applied to the DLPFC.

messages.content:
Statement: In a randomized sham-controlled cross-over study, 60 subjects (30 Males) received sham and active tDCS in two subgroups (anode left/cathode right and anode right/cathode left) of the DLPFC.
